First awarded in 2001, the '''Green Chemistry Award''' is presented biennially by the [[Royal Society of Chemistry]] (RSC) for advances in environmentally focused chemistry.<ref name="RSC website">{{cite web|title=Green Chemistry Award|url=http://www.rsc.org/ScienceAndTechnology/Awards/GreenChemistry/|website=Royal Society of Chemistry}}</ref> In addition to a prize of £2000, winners of the award complete a UK based lecture tour.<ref name="RSC website"/> The Award was last presented in 2016.
